                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The text runs parallel to the fibers. The unskilled hand sometimes leaves large spaces between the letters of one single word. The papyrus, tapering towards the bottom, is only damaged by a few holes, but the text is difficult to read because the ink of some words has run. Also on the verso side there are ink traces visible, probably due to it having lain on top of another papyrus that had not yet completely dried.</p>
